The case against 19-year-old Forest High School pupil Mohammad Mawela has been postponed. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - The case against 19-year-old Forest High School pupil Mohammad Mawela has been postponed on Friday. Mawela is accused of stabbing 16-year-old fellow pupil Daniel Bakwela to death at the school premises. READ: Police to monitor Forest high school Mawela made a brief appearance at the Johannesburg magistrate's court. He said three boys, whom he accuses of being gang members, attacked him and said the murder weapon belonged to the deceased. Bakwela was killed while two others were wounded in the fight.